<div style=""><a href="http://maps.google.com/?bounds=45.389771,-122.829208|45.659647,-122.404175&q=1969+NE+42nd" target="_BLANK">Velo Cult, 1969 NE 42nd</a> <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=1969+NE+42nd&by=6:30+p.m.&on=06/10/13" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="viewpp2013_files/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a> (we will meet downstairs)</div>
6:30pm<div style="">
<em>Interested in touring or camping by bike, but have questions, concerns, or just need guidance? Come to this free workshop put on by Cycle Wild board member Erinne and learn about the right gear, how to carry it, tips for the road, ideas of places to travel, and stories from other trips. 
<br>
<br>Women and Trans folks only at this workshop, please.</em>
<br>Erinne, e<span>rinne.goodell<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/at.gif" alt=" at ">cyclewild<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/dotorg.gif" alt=" daht oh are gee"></span>, <a href="http://www.cyclewild.org/">Cycle Wild</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/calforum.php?id=3790" title="0 messages"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/forum.gif" alt="[forum]"></a>
</div></dd>
<dt style=""><a name="10-3686" style="">PARKS 2 PARKS EPIC NITE RIDE</a>
<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/viewpp2013.php#10-3686"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/chain.gif" alt="Link" title="Link to this event"></a>
</dt><dd><div style=""><a href="http://maps.google.com/?bounds=45.389771,-122.829208|45.659647,-122.404175&q=SE+28th+between+SE+Division+%26+Clinton" target="_BLANK">Piccolo Park, SE 28th between SE Division &amp; Clinton</a> <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=SE+28th+between+SE+Division+%26+Clinton&by=7:30+p.m.&on=06/10/13" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="viewpp2013_files/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a></div>
7:30pm<div style="">
<em>Mellow ride from park to park all night long. Discover under-appreciated parks with plenty of play time at each- different parks every year. In past years we've had 30 people in one tree, a team of pandas playing frisbee, a cuddle party in a miniature park, saxophone along the bluffs, skinny-dipping in a heated pool, among other adventures. 
<br>
<br>This ride is not a loop, and it will go late. BYOB, hula hoops, blankets, and park gear. It's a slow-ass pace but often of epic length for those who stay til the end.
<br>
<br>Douglas Adams says: Always remember your towel!</em>
<br>AnomaLily, a<span>nomalily<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/at.gif" alt=" at ">gmail<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/dotcom.gif" alt=" daht comm"></span>, <a href="http://www.anomalily.net/">www.anomalily.net</a>, t<span>weet <img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/at.gif" alt=" at ">anomalily for ride details</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/calforum.php?id=3686" title="1 message, newest 2013-06-05"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/forum.gif" alt="[forum]"></a>
</div></dd>
</dl>
