<dt style=""><a name="15-3683" style="">BANKS-VERNONIA CAMPOUT</a>
<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/viewpp2013.php#15-3683"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/chain.gif" alt="Link" title="Link to this event"></a>
</dt><dd><div style=""><a href="http://maps.google.com/?bounds=45.389771,-122.829208|45.659647,-122.404175&q=100+SW+Adams+Ave%2C+Hillsboro" target="_BLANK">Hatfield Government Center MAX Station in Hillsboro, 100 SW Adams Ave, Hillsboro</a> <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=100+SW+Adams+Ave&Dcty=HI&by=12:00+p.m.&on=06/15/13" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="viewpp2013_files/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a></div>
12:00pm, The trip will end on Sunday in Hillsboro mid-afternoon.<div style="">
<em>This is a delightfully mellow overnight trip, perfect for beginning bike trippers &amp; seasoned enthusiasts alike. &nbsp;We'll meet up at the last Max station in Hillsboro, ride an easy 12 miles up to Banks on scenic country roads, then we'll jump onto the Banks-Vernonia trail, a 21-mile car-free paved path that meanders along the river through farms and forests. &nbsp;We'll arrive in quaint Vernonia, pitch our tents, and end the day with some burgers and beers at the pub!
