8:15pm<div style="">
<em>Meet at People's to gather provisions for the short night. We ride right after sunset at 9:04pm. The moment of solstice is 10:04pm PST this year. At one of the first few stops on the ride there will be talk on exactly what that means for anyone interested. 
<br>Ride a comfortable bike because the ride ends at sunrise on the first morning of summer at 5:22 am. There will be stops and hills, and the ride will end at a nice spot to watch the sun come up. Bring warm clothes. This is not a loop, nor is it a fast ride. We'll take our time; after all, we've got all night.</em>
