<dt style=""><a name="24-3787" style="">THE RENT IS TOO DAMN HIGH RIDE</a>
<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/viewpp2013.php#24-3787"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/chain.gif" alt="Link" title="Link to this event"></a>
</dt><dd><img src="viewpp2013_files/3787.JPG" height="125" width="166.666666667" align="left" alt="">
<div style=""><a href="http://maps.google.com/?bounds=45.389771,-122.829208|45.659647,-122.404175&q=N+Center+Court+St+and+N+Hassalo+St" target="_BLANK">Rose Quarter, N Center Court St and N Hassalo St</a> <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=N+Center+Court+St+and+N+Hassalo+St&by=5:30+p.m.&on=06/24/13" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="viewpp2013_files/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a> (near the fountains by the Rose Garden)</div>
5:30pm - 8:00pm, ride at 6 pm, food by 7:30<div style="">
<em>Finding a room to rent in Portland sucks - we've got the second-lowest apartment vacancy rate in the country. But thanks to bikes, things are about to get better: in the next two years, hundreds of new apartments designed for middle-class, low-car families will be opening up in the central city, hopefully helping keep rents under control for all of us. Michael Andersen and Zef Wagner will lead a ride to the awesomest and ugliest of these new buildings and a conversation about ways the city can keep bike-friendly rents low. Bring cash for a wonkalicious food cart meal at the end.</em>
<br>Mike Andersen &amp; Zef Wagner, m<span>ike.andersen<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/at.gif" alt=" at ">gmail<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/dotcom.gif" alt=" daht comm"></span>, 503-928-0444&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/calforum.php?id=3787" title="0 messages"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/forum.gif" alt="[forum]"></a>
</div></dd>
<dt style=""><a name="24-3800" style="">THE DREAM OF THE 1890S IS ALIVE IN NW PORTLAND</a>
<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/viewpp2013.php#24-3800"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/chain.gif" alt="Link" title="Link to this event"></a>
</dt><dd><div style=""><a href="http://maps.google.com/?bounds=45.389771,-122.829208|45.659647,-122.404175&q=1819+NW+Everett+Street%2C+Portland+OR" target="_BLANK">NW Cultural Center, 1819 NW Everett Street, Portland OR</a> <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=1819+NW+Everett+Street+OR&Dcty=PO&by=5:30+p.m.&on=06/24/13" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="viewpp2013_files/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a> (Meet on the Cultural Center's front steps)</div>
5:30pm - 7:30pm, Stay longer for beer, good eats, and great conversation at Lucky Lab Beer Hall! (NW location)<div style="">
<em>Join the Young Professionals in Transportation as we explore the historical sites of NW Portland and Old Town on a bike tour designed by the Historical Preservation League of Oregon. &nbsp;Local historians will guide us to remnants of the Lewis &amp; Clark Exposition, weird public works projects, Croatian-Irish churches, and architectural quirks of the NW. &nbsp;We'll even step inside a few buildings to check out them out from the inside out. &nbsp;Ride will be a mostly-flat 6 miles at a cruising pace and end with beers at Lucky Lab Beer Hall. Period costumes strongly encouraged - get yer bloomers on!</em>
<br>Evan Corey, e<span>van.corey<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/at.gif" alt=" at ">gmail<img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/dotcom.gif" alt=" daht comm"></span>, <a href="http://yptransportation.org/%20%20and%20%20https://www.facebook.com/pages/YPT-Portland/167629380055995">Young Professionals in Transportation</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/calforum.php?id=3800" title="0 messages"><img border="0" src="viewpp2013_files/forum.gif" alt="[forum]"></a>
